@node "Introduction" "Introduction"
@next "Requirements"
@prev "Main"
@{b}Introduction:@{ub}

MLogBook is HAM Radio logging program which is in beta version. With this
program you can save all your QSO's. MLogBook has many @{"features" link "Features" 0} but a few of
it is not available yet. This MLogBook allow to log only 100000 QSO (internal
limitation made by me :) I'd like to ask every user of this program for any
comments, bug reports or good words.
@endnode

@node "Requirements" "Requirements"
@next "Installation"
@prev "Introduction"
@{b}Requirements:@{ub}

   @{b}Hardware:@{ub}
   Amiga with KS 2.1+,
   Hard Disk,
   2MB Fast RAM

   @{b}Software:@{ub}
   MUI 3.8
   BetterString.mcc (included)
   NList.mcc        (included)
   SpeedBar.mcc     (included)
@endnode

@node "Installation" "Installation"
@next "Usage"
@prev "Requirements"
@{b}Installation:@{ub}

 Use installation script or:

 1. Extract archive of MLogBook.
 2. Copy all files from MLogBook/Libs/MUI to MUI:Libs/MUI directory.
@endnode

