@node "First Start" "First Start"
@next "Normal Logging"
@prev "Usage"
@{b}First start@{ub}

  If you put any CallBook data file (CSV format) in CallBook dir and start,
MLogBook will scan this file and make index for it (for fast access to
datas). @{b}You should be patience because this operation is very slow.@{ub}
  MLogBook will paste data to "Comments" field from CallBook, only from
columns: 1, 2 and 5 (and from 6 to "Locator").
  If you don't want to use CallBook then remove SP.CSV file from CallBook
dir. I added SP.CSV file which is a part of SP9TNM's Polish CallBook but the
one have'nt address, zip and phone fields (in original one these fields
exists) for privacy protection. The original file you can find in Internet
and it's in DBF file format so after downloading it you should convert it to
ASCII. I used for it DBF2ASC program which you can find in Aminet.
@endnode

@node "Normal Logging" "Normal Logging"
@next "Contest Logging"
@prev "First Start"
@{b}Normal logging:@{ub}

After start you can type any callsign (e.g. SP9WUN) in "3:Callsign" field.
"3" means that when you press @{b}Right Amiga and 3@{ub} - you'll activate this field.
This is usefull when you dislike to using @{b}TAB@{ub} key. Also you should know that
@{b}TAB@{ub} key don't enter data. It mean that when you type SP9WUN in Callsign field
and press @{b}TAB@{ub} you'll only change active field. If you want to enter SP9WUN
you shoult press @{b}Enter@{ub} key (on keyboard ;). If you'll fill a fields you
should press "@{b}Enter@{ub}" button or press @{b}RightAmiga-E@{ub}. I hope it's clear. Data
and Time fields will be set to current when you press @{b}Enter@{ub} key.
@endnode

@node "Contest Logging" "Contest Logging"
@next "Editing Entry"
@prev "Normal Logging"
@{b}Contest logging@{ub}

If you want to work in contest you should create new preference file. So open
Preference window and type in @{b}Preference Filename@{ub} field new name of your
settings. You can type contest name e.g. MLogBook.cqww

Now you have to change @{b}LogBook Filename@{ub} field, e.g. cqww_2000.log

Next step is to set @{b}Log Mode@{ub} cycle gadget from "Normal" to contest name which
you need. After it MLogBook will read contest Rules File from Rules
directory.

You can to do own Rules Files. Look into available files and read comments to
know how. I wonder if you'll send it to me with your agreement to join it to
MLogBook distribution archive Now you can save setting and begin work in
contest.
@endnode

@node "Editing Entry" "Editing Entry"
@next "Import"
@prev "Contest Logging"
@{b}Editing entry:@{ub}

When you @{b}doubleclick@{ub} on any entry you will see it on down part of window. You
can change what you want and press "@{b}Enter@{ub}" button like in normal logging
mode. If you can change date or time in entry you should open @{b}Settings Window
@{ub}and enable displaying @{b}Date@{ub} and @{b}Time@{ub} field.

You can also enable @{b}Settings/Lock DateTime@{ub} from menu to disable time and date
updating after pressing @{b}Enter@{ub}.
@endnode

@node "Import" "Import"
@next "Export"
@prev "Editing Entry"
@{b}Import:@{ub}

 With this item you can import logs created by:
 - AmiCom (Amiga Packet Radio terminal program - tested with 2.3)
 - SuperDuper (tested with 7.08 version)
 - ADFI (not full implemented)
@endnode

@node "Export" "Export"
@next "Undo"
@prev "Import"
@{b}Export:@{ub}

You can export current log to ADFI exchange file.
@endnode

@node "Undo" "Undo"
@next "Find"
@prev "Export"
@{b}Undo:@{ub}

Only 1 level of undo is available.
@endnode

@node "Find" "Find"
@next "Delete"
@prev "Undo"
@{b}Find:@{ub}

Type any string which you like to find in current log and press @{b}Enter@{ub} button.
@endnode

@node "Delete" "Delete"
@next "Rescan Log"
@prev "Find"
@{b}Delete:@{ub}

This function remove all selected lines.
@endnode

@node "Rescan Log" "Rescan Log"
@next "Shortcuts"
@prev "Delete"
@{b}Rescan Log@{ub}

This feature is usefull for creating statistics of logbook and for contest
working. If you use this tool MLogBook will rescan all callsigns saved in log
and fill @{b}1@{ub}, and @{b}3@{ub} fields in Log Table for current Rules file. Thanks for it
you'll get prefixes in column "@{b}1@{ub}" and WAZ zones in "@{b}2@{ub}" for CQWW contest type.
@endnode

@node "Shortcuts" "Shortcuts"
@prev "Rescan Log"
@{b}Shortcuts:@{ub}

 Amiga-1  Band
 Amiga-2  Mode
 Amiga-3  Callsign
 Amiga-4  RSTs (Report sent)
 Amiga-5  Rems (Remarx sent)
 Amiga-6  RSTr (Report received)
 Amiga-7  Remr (Remarx received)
 Amiga-8  Locator
 Amiga-9  Comment
 Amiga-E  Enter
 Amiga-T  Test
 Amiga-L  Load
 Amiga-S  Save
 Amiga-C  Copy
 Amiga-V  Paste
 Amiga-X  Cut
 Amiga-Z  Undo
 Amiga-A  Select All
 Amiga-F  Find
 Amiga-K  Configuration
 Amiga-L  Lock Date/Time
 Amiga-?  About
 Amiga-Q  Quit
@endnode

